{% ifequal name "phelex" %}
<h1>Phelex Foundation</h1>
<p><img src="/images/logo_phelex.gif"><br />
<a href="http://www.phelex.com">www.phelex.com</a></p>

<p><b>Description</b>:The Phelex Foundation is a 501(c)(3) operating charity based in Massachusetts, the United States. Founded in 1995 by a group of Boston-area residents, the foundation actively promotes basic education for financially, socially or physically disadvantaged children in the poverty-stricken regions of rural Asia. It focuses on establishing self-sustainable funding sources through school operated work-study programs, educational partnerships, communal participation and volunteerism. The Phelex Foundation has three operating divisions:</p>

<ul style="font-size:90%">
  <li>The Phelex Sustainable Tuition Aid Program (1995)</li>
  <li>The Phelex Institute for the Study of Rural Education (2000)</li>
  <li>International Youth Urban-suburban Cross-cultural Exchange (2003)</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Interactions with Givology</b>: Recently, Phelex has been working hard in Sichuan, China to partner up with national organizations such as the China Foundation for the Handicapped and the Beijing Foundation of Youth Development to track all children affected by the earthquake. Phelex posts individual student profiles from sponsored schools, as well as sustainable tuition projects from Sichuan and other parts of China. For areas without a computer or Internet, Phelex always donates a computer to their partner schools, hence providing an easy method for teachers and students to maintain communication with Givology. </p>
{% endifequal %}

{% ifequal name "peach" %}
<h1>Peach Foundation</h1>
<p><img src="/images/logo_peach.gif"><br />
<a href="http://www.PeachFoundationUSA.org">www.PeachFoundationUSA.org</a></p>

<p><b>Description</b>: Peach stands for Promoting Education, Art, and Community Harvest. Created by a group of U.S. citizens in 2001, Peach Foundation is a California non-profit organization with no political or religious affiliations. The Peach Foundation was formed to help children from the poorest parts of China obtain an opportunity to complete a college education. The Foundation makes arrangement with local regions to elect qualified teachers, who are then entrusted to recommend students based on financial need and academic potential. After a stringent evaluation process, selected students will receive financial assistance directly in the form of a scholarship. The teachers from the local regions are responsible for communicating with the Peach Foundation and for handling matters related to this task. Each year, appointed volunteers representing the Foundation will travel to various regions in China at their own expense to evaluate the program. Since 2002, Peach has also published its own annual reports that summarize their progress.</p>

<p><b>Interactions with Givology</b>: Givology and PEACH are very complementary, as one offers a platform for expansion and visibility for the other. Together, we work to fund an increasingly large base of students in China. PEACH has offered an initial twenty student profiles of $250.00 in requested donation per child, and maintains regular visits to track the progress of the student. </p>
{% endifequal %}

{% ifequal name "zhuhai" %}
<h1>Zhuhai Charity Foundation</h1>
<p><a href="http://www.zhcsh.org.cn/index.asp">www.zhcsh.org.cn/index.asp</a></p>

<p><b>Description:</b> Through Zhuhai Charity Federation, we team up with Ahelp, a non-profit NGO found in 2004 focusing on helping education for low-income students that channel funds through the school. The Zhuhai Charity Foundation was established on October 30, 2003. It focuses very broadly on helping organizations and constituents alleviate poverty through channeling donations, especially post-disasters.Zhuhai Charity Foundation works in primarily to "help overcome educational obstacles," "save orphans," "cover medical fees," "save the poor," and "save the handicapped" (translated). On the other hand, Ahelp sets up projects for schools and children, specifically. In the past, it has helped build over forty libraries for schools and mobilized visits to 600 villages and 6,000 student families in 3 provinces. In total, it has delivered over two million yuan delivered to schools and students. It has:</p>

<ul style="font-size:90%">
    <li>Over 80,00 forum members worldwide</li>
    <li>Over 500 volunteers worldwide</li>
    <li>Over 1000 donors worldwide</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Interactions with Givology:</b> Givology works with Zhuhai Charity Federation, a working partner of Ahelp, to assist the schools and student populations in rural Southern China. The actual volunteers and information collected for our site are primarily associated with Ahelp.</p>
{% endifequal %}

