<p><b>Description</b>: Ahelp was founded in 2004 in China. It is a non-profit NGO focusing on helping education for low-income students that channel funds through the school. Serving as a bridge between donors and children in need, it has had a track record of helping over 2,200 children obtain long-term education from middle through high school (with a focus on high school tuition fees due to Nine Year Compulsory Education Act in China). Ahelp also sets up projects for its schools. In the past, it has helped build over forty libraries for schools and mobilized visits to 600 villages and 6,000 student families in 3 provinces. In total, it has delivered over two million Yuan delivered to schools and students. Some numbers that it reports:</p>

